.TH I3SPACE 1 "June 2026" "i3space 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
i3space \- workspace overview for i3
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B i3space
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows active i3 workspaces per monitor in a horizontal strip. Config-agnostic: reads state via i3 IPC.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-toggle
Open interactive overview (requires i3 and X11).
.TP
.B \-\-print-active
Print active workspaces grouped by output (JSON).
.TP
.B \-\-output \fINAME\fR
Filter \-\-print-active to one X output.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print help.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/i3space/i3space
Main configuration.
.SH EXAMPLE
bindsym \-\-release $mod+Shift+Tab exec \-\-no-startup-id i3space \-\-toggle
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR i3 (1),
.BR i3-msg (1),
.BR picom (1)
